Package <Unnamed>

Interface Summary
GameObject This interface serves as the base for all GameObjects in this Game.
Movable The Movable interface is implemented by GameObjects to give them functionality and capabilities required for the Objects to move, and signify to the Engine that this Object can move.
Solid This is the Solid interface.
World<E> The World interface is implemented by classes in order to give them functionality required by the Game Engine such as GameObject manipulation and handling.
 

Class Summary
AbstractGameObject This class is the abstract class that is used as the super class for all GameObjects.
AbstractMovable This is the abstract class for the Movable interface that gives its subclasses all the functionality of a normal GameObject, but it can also move around its enclosing World Object.
AbstractWorld<E> The AbstractWorld class.
